HEADWORD: major suit
<hw>major suit</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Bridge)</fld> <def>A suit of
playing cards which has higher scoring value; specifically, either
spades or hearts. Contrasted with a <contr>minor suit</contr>, being
either diamonds or clubs.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

